Ordering online is a nightmare, we’ve ordered about a dozen times in the past 3 months and they get the order correct about 40% of the time. The worst part of online ordering is not necessarily the inaccuracy, its more that they force you to wait in the normal line to pick it up, where every other Taco Bell has a (no line) pickup station The owner of this restaurant reached out regarding a former complaint of order accuracy and having to wait to pickup food, but orders continue to be inaccurate and we continue to have to go to the normal line- so it seems as if they just threw the complaint away + 60% of our order gets thrown away

(Edit: taking a star off because of an abysmal experience trying to order through their website) Eh, it's Taco Bell. It's not great but also not the worst by any means. You go in knowing you're going to sacrifice quality for a better price point. Besides being one of the only Taco Bells within range of the T, there's nothing special about this location. However, every time I've been here there have been long waits for food, sometimes approaching 10 minutes. Honestly, if you're craving Tex-Mex and neither time nor money are pressing concerns, head down Cambridge St. to Lone Star.

I have ordered thru uber eats from them 4 times now, trying to give them a chance to be better but they have consistently shown no improvement. I understand as a fellow restaurant worker that you want to take care of the customers that are in the store already and not thru a third party delivery. but between the delivery fee service fees and taxes it almost doubles the order cost and those of us who order thru them are customers as well paying your wages and keeping your business afloat. we should therefore not be cast aside as unimportant simply because we are not in front of you and made to wait over an hour for you to input t he order or in this case not confirm the order on the tablet so my food gets cold sitting there and I end up having to call the restaurant to make sure you do your job correctly. so now my food will be cold late and at this point I do not even want it. So thanks for ruining a former customers day.
